      <p>Adam Ewan is a British actor working in theatre, film and television. After graduating from the Bristol Old Vic Theatre School, Adam's first role was in the British independent film 'Morris: A Life with Bells On' (Twist Films), a spoof documentary about the quintessentially English pastime of Morris dancing.</p>
      <p>Further credits include: Small Island (National Theatre), My Country (National Theatre), Pride (Proud Films Production Ltd), Endeavour (Mammoth Screen), Fleabag (BBC TV), Fantastic Beasts - The Crimes of Grindelwald (Warner Bros), The Honourable History of Friar Bacon and Friar Bungay (Shakespeare's Globe), The Colour of Magic (Mob Films), He Kills Coppers (Ecosse), A Christian Turn'd Turk (Shakepeare's Globe) - see Biography for further information.</p>
